  "prompt": "Are there any TV series similar to How to Get Away with Murder?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several TV series that have similarities to \"How to Get Away with Murder,\" particularly in terms of themes like legal drama, suspense, and complex characters. Here are a few recommendations:\n\n1. **Scandal** - Created by Shonda Rhimes, this political thriller follows Olivia Pope, a crisis manager, as she handles various scandals and secrets in Washington, D.C.\n\n2. **Suits** - This legal drama revolves around a talented college dropout who starts working as a law associate at a prestigious firm, despite not having a law degree.\n\n3. **The Good Wife** - After her husband's political scandal, Alicia Florrick returns to work as a defense attorney, navigating complex legal cases and office politics.\n\n4. **Damages** - With intense legal battles and moral ambiguity, this series follows the relationship between a ruthless lawyer and her prot\u00e9g\u00e9.\n\n5. **Better Call Saul** - A prequel to \"Breaking Bad,\" this series explores the transformation of Jimmy McGill into the morally ambiguous lawyer Saul Goodman.\n\n6. **For the People** - This legal drama focuses on young lawyers working on opposite sides of high-profile cases in the Southern District of New York Federal Court.\n\n7. **The Fix** - A legal drama about an attorney who, after losing a high-profile case, gets a second chance to prosecute the same defendant.\n\n8. **The Practice** - A legal drama that follows the lives of defense attorneys at a Boston law firm.\n\nThese shows offer similar elements of legal intrigue, complex characters, and suspenseful storytelling that fans of \"How to Get Away with Murder\" might enjoy.",
